<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Introduction</span></p>
<p class="para">Hello everyone and thank you for coming to the NieR:Theatrical Orchestra 12020 concert. I’m Keiichi Okabe, the composer for the NieR series. At all of our past shows, I enjoyed seeing your faces and hearing your warm applause from the stage.
<br>
However, today I’m here in this gigantic hall talking to a camera, unable to see any of you, left to imagine you clapping on the other side of your monitors. The world is facing a serious crisis right now, and this morning it snowed really heavily in Tokyo—unusual for this time of year.
<br>
I truly believe we’ve only been able to overcome all these obstacles and hold this concert thanks to the hard work of our staff and the support of everyone watching right now. Thank you so much. The voice actors we heard from before the concert will reappear later on to perform various scenes. We will also get to hear the angelic voices of Emi Evans and J’Nique Nicole.
<br>
Today’s music will be performed by conductor Takeshi Ooi and the Tokyo Philharmonic Orchestra, with ~Barzz~ Chorus of a game music specialists handling chorus duties. Oh, and the footage you’ll see on the screen behind us was all made for this conceit by Yoko Taro, along with the scenes you’ll hear later. I really think all these elements will combine to make this a very special show. I’ve of course been looking forward to today, but I hope more than anything that those of you watching at home enjoy this unique concert, one that’s worthy of marking NieR’s tenth anniversary.
<br>
Anyway, that’s enough talking for now. It’s time for the NieR Thea-Theatrical… Let me give that another shot! It’s time for the NieR:Theatrical Orchestra 12020 concert.</p>
