<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Story of Two Siblings</p>
<p class="title"><span class="title-box">Section 1 (Ashes of Dreams)</p>
<p class="para">Snow is falling.
<br>It should be summer, but I see my breath.
<br>I rub my freezing hands together, and my little sister does the same.
<br>A little smile floats my way. She looks pale... We haven’t eaten in a while.
<br>All I could do for her back then was hold her fight.
<br>
<br>If there is a god, then I have a request:
<br>Give my sister some food and a warm place to sleep... and medicine to cure her sickness.
<br>If you do that, I promise I’ll never be selfish or say bad things about other people again.
<br>Please, God... You can do what you want to me.
<br>
<br>Now that it’s over, I curse my foolishness. Where did I go wrong?
<br>A little sister desperate to survive. A world destroyed so a promise might be kept.
<br>A thousand-year promise, sullied with lies. That form of life held no salvation. That path was corrupt.
<br>This is the story of a kind sister and her foolish brother... who tried to live in a world without meaning.</p>
